mlx-gen is an independent, from-scratch Rust reimplementation of on-device MLX
inference for generative image and video models. No source code from the
projects listed below is copied into the shipped Rust crates; they are
gratefully acknowledged as the architectural lineage, references, and parity
baselines it was developed against:

  * Apple MLX               https://github.com/ml-explore/mlx           (MIT)
  * mlx-rs                  https://crates.io/crates/mlx-rs             (Apache-2.0 OR MIT)
  * mflux (Filip Strand)    https://github.com/filipstrand/mflux        (MIT)
  * Apple mlx-examples      https://github.com/ml-explore/mlx-examples  (MIT)
  * Hugging Face Diffusers  https://github.com/huggingface/diffusers    (Apache-2.0)

Vendored third-party source
---------------------------

One frozen third-party reference implementation IS redistributed with this
crate, under `_vendor/`. It is a dev-only parity oracle: it is Python, it is
never imported by any Rust crate, and it is not part of any shipped bundle.

  * Mage-Flow reference     https://github.com/microsoft/Mage           (MIT)
    `_vendor/mage_flow/` — verbatim copy of the `mage_flow/` package at commit
    df7f84d9f8fc991d189d929f03cff623b430a4a2, redistributed under the MIT
    license reproduced at `_vendor/mage_flow/LICENSE`.
    Copyright (c) 2026 Microsoft. See `_vendor/VENDORED.md` for provenance,
    the pinned reference environment, and what was excluded.

Model weights are not distributed with mlx-gen and remain subject to the
licenses of their respective providers.
